-- EU's Van Rompuy: decisions on Euro group head, ESM and ECB posts in July
-- 
-- Fri Jun 29, 2012 8:27am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/06/29/us-eu-summit-rompuy-idUSBRE85S0PT20120629

 

 BRUSSELS  (Reuters) - Euro zone leaders agreed on Friday to bend their aid rules to shore up banks and bring down the borrowing costs of stricken members like Italy and Spain, in a sign the bloc is adopting a more flexible approach to solving its two-year old debt crisis. 
